		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Gameplay posts from Gordon Wrinn</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=126811" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037609.html">Monks: Human vs Iksar---Please respond Abashi</a><P>

Up to this point, the only differences between characters of different races but same classes have been racial differences. Never has a class been different for one race than it is for another--to me this seems logical and straightforward, and I see no reason to change it.<P>

<B>Previously, with only one class capable of becoming a monk, balancing the monk class on the basis of race was not difficult. However, the inclusion of the Iksar, with many different racial attributes, has made this a bit harder.<P>
 
Infravision and regen make life much easier for the young Iksar, which leaves us with a need to validate humans as a monk class. In addition, monks are the only race that get an AC bonus based upon their race. This leaves them already getting one just by virtue of being a monk, and now another because they are also an Iksar.<P> 

In this case, we decided that in addition to including the expected XP and faction issues, we've also made it so that Iksar monks will not be as "good" at *being* monks as humans. It's not by a large extreme, but human monks will always be better at doing what monks do: dealing damage.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037610.html">Kunark restores my love for EQ</a><P>

The framerates are a bit slow, sounds are all screwed up, but overall the graphics and new creatures are excellent. Kunark restores my love for EQ Verant, Kudos, for me you made the game fun again.<P>

<B>Glad to hear it Jimmy, thanks a lot. And don't worry, we'll get those sounds fixed up soon :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037874.html">One tech support phone number for 200,000 plus customers?</a><P>

Is Verant going to add "a" second phone number to call now that the masses of subscribers have gotten way out of control for 7 technicians to handle? Trying to talk to a live Verant employee is like trying to talk to a live KROQ employee.<P>

<B>It's one phone number, but it certainly is more than one line. The line rolls over to the next available technician.<P> 

The majority of EverQuest technical support occurs at installation time. Once people can get in game, only a very small percentage ever need tech support again. Certainly there are cases where that number and percentage increase, such as in the case of ROK, however the number of people that we have maning the phones do a very good job of keeping up with the load.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037887.html">ressurect line stealth nerfed again?</a><P>

since last patch ive been getting complaints of little to absolutely no exp upon lv 39 recissitate<P>

<B>I've heard a couple reports of this (thanks to those who emailed me). No intentional change was made to this line, but I've forwarded to the test team to check it out.<P>
 
-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037914.html">Gorillas in Burning Woods....</a><P>

The Gorillas in the Burning Woods are not animals.... Is this as intended? If so, why? There is absolutely no point for furthering the animal-line in the Druid's spell list if there are no animals on Kunark. To tell the truth, I have yet to find one creature that is an animal...<P>

<B>Actually none of the Gorillas are animals as I recall, and I believe that these particular ones are undead.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037929.html">Why doesn't hide wipe the hate list?</a><P>

Now, rogues are basicly group-unfriendly monks why are equip dependent, and have no way to escape death other than run. I think it would be a GREAT idea to make hide wipe the hate list, just as Monks can FD.<P>

<B>Because we didn't implement it as an escape spell. It used to do this in beta, but it trivialized combat and provided too big of an advantage to those who could invis.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037959.html">Timourous Deep doesn't seem too be itemized</a><P>

just wanted too point this out since i've not even been able to get a coin from a bandit<P>

<B>No coin? That certainly doesn't sound right. I've sent it to the EQLive team for investigation. Much thanks.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037967.html">No refund yet! How is this not a crime?</a><P>

This might sound a bit harsh but I feel pretty strongly about people charging my creditcard for something they find out they cant deliver and then not refunding my money IMMEDIATELY!<P>

<B>We apologize for any delay. We are processing refunds as fast as possible in the order that the requests were received.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037784-4.html">Class Envy Posts.</a><P>

Personally, I'm glad to see it. He NEVER said that verant wouldn't address broken spells/songs or other issues with classes/races and such. He just said that he's not going to devote time to pure class envy posts. "My class isn't as good as my friends class" is a LOT different than "Alchemy costs WAY too much to be a usefull skill"<P>

<B>Indeed. As I mentioned in the original post, we'll certainly read them and comment from time to time when something can be serviced by it, but we need to focus on adding content to the game and correcting problems that we can all more or less agree on, rather than engaging in the constant debate over class-balance.<P> 

Certainly if someone brings up an issue that we agree with, we will act. We have done this on many occasions over the past few months, correcting many balance issues that were brought up by players and that upon investigation, we agreed with. We will continue to do this, but I think that our attentiveness over the past few months has caused a bit of "squeaky wheel syndrome".<P> 

Again I really apologize that there is no way that we could suddenly have everyone be happy. Believe me, if there was, we would jump at the chance.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037910.html">Faction Issues on Kunark</a><P>

<B>In the interest of gameplay, we've decided to take out the faction modifier that makes Dark Elven worshippers of Solusek Ro and Bristlebane KOS to NPCs in the Venril Sathir faction. This is on test now and should go live at the next patch. <P>

Providing that Dark Elven worshippers of these deities haven't done anything to further anger Venril Sathir, they'll be able to use the outpost then.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

Your faction with PeopleWhoDontThinkVerantListensToTheirCustomers got Better!<P>

<B>ROFL :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

It is still a poor move on Verants part to make Dungeon factions tied to the only DE, Troll and Ogre outpost on Kunark. If you are going to keep it this way, put some quests and **** in those dungeons for evil classes/races, and make it so the stuff in there doesnt KOS them.<P>

<B>Well the dungeon-based factions are going to stay, as they are fairly important for the ways things work on Kunark, the idea for quests in there is a good one.<P> 

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
